Sen. Dick Durbin at the infant Welfare Society of Chicago, July 19, 2004.
(Photo by Tim Boyle/Getty Images)(CNSNews.com) - Sen. Dick Durbin (D.-Ill.), the Senate Democratic Whip, sent out a pair of tweets on Thursday recognizing “Black Maternal Health Week” and expressing his commitment to supporting the health of African American mothers and their babies.
“In the U.S., African American women are still 2.5x more likely than white women to die as a result of pregnancy,” Durbin said in the first tweet.
“We can & must do more to protect women of color & their babies,” Durbin said.
“I remain committed to doing everything I can to protect black maternal health.”The second tweet Durbin sent out included a video clip of him delivering a message stating his support for African American mothers.